<br>
I am a rising magician from the grand capital of Odus, who is just now earning her keep in the lands. I have learned a great deal by travelling and adventuring on my own, although magicians are never truly alone.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :thumb --><img src=http://www.spacespider.net/emo/thumbsup.gif ALT=":thumb"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
However, I  am starting to recognize the need for family and friendship and have a burning desire to help others achieve their goals and attain happiness.<br>
<br>
I am a fast learner and am from a wealthy family so I seek no hand me downs or training, just a group with whom to share adventures with and explore new parts of the world that I would never see by my lonesome.  I have learned that there is nothing more satisfying than to help others acheive what they desire in the world of Norrath.  It is the only thing that brings happiness to this Erudite's face.<br>
<br>
Yours truly,<br>
<br>
Lady Kimberly<br>
Of the Gate Callers<br>
___________<br>
<br>
OOC<br>
<br>
Hi everyone. Kimberly was born on October 21, 2001, a long long time ago when the server first opened.  I only played her a little but then moved back to my main character (a cleric) on my server's resident end game guild until I decided to retire shortly before PoP came out. (I have experience in all zones and fights up to Shei, Cursed, Emperor and Seru pre-POP).<br>
 <br>
As a player I learned a long time ago that getting a good drop isn't nearly as fun as helping out someone else, and from the general feel of the community I believe a lot of you feel that way.<br>
<br>
I'm leveling steadily, but am enjoying a relaxed pace. I have sufficient gear and am not looking for any kind of 'twinking' or 'powerleveling' as I am trying to learn my new class as best I can with the means at my disposal. (/thank join mage and Jarlork in particular)<br>
<br>
I think its best to learn about guilds based on the members of that guild and how they act in game while grouping with them, but I am afraid at my lower level (mid 20s now) I will not meet enough people to make a sound judgement.<br>
<br>
I am more than willing to level up to a required level but in the meantime would like to do some research on guilds that are a decent size ( I find a good sized guild tends to more grouping possibilities), who values roleplaying (why else would you be on Firiona Vie?) and who raids regularly but does not focus exlcusively on raiding, and generally is at the HateFear/Kunark/early Velious level of the game since that is where I will be soon and am very comfortable with.<br>
<br>
Please let me know if I can be of service to your guild and feel free to send me a /tell in game. I love meeting new people and will always answer a call for help.<br>
<br>
Thanks ever so much for reading.<br>
<br>
Kim<br>
