Welcome Kimberly,<br>
<br>
The Court of the Crosswinds is a small to medium guild that values Roleplaying, family, and fun. We try to maintain a balance of all the things that make Norrath such a exciting place to live. We are very open and do not force any person to participate in any activity they do not wish to. We have no strict RP requirements, but we encourage staying in character for day to day conversation. We are also a good aligned guild, but allow &quot;converted&quot; evil characters that have met certain strict requirements involving faction and RP storyline. We very much value helping others and try to ensure that our interactions with people in guild and out of guild reflect that.<br>
<br>
As far as raid strength goes, the Court has members of all levels, as we have a low level requirement. However, the core of our raid force consists of people between 40-62. We have completed many of the easier epics, and are working our way toward some of the more difficult ones. We hope to be capable of venturing into the halls of testing within the next one to two months. Our scheduled events usually consist of one weekend event and one weekday smaller event. However, pickup events are fairly common for any that wish to attend. We are basically learning as we go, and take pride in accomplishing things with smaller numbers of people then is normally suggested. We are not a Zerg guild.<br>
